Durban - A 39-year-old man was arrested and charged during a raid at a premises in the Point area on Monday. Police recovered 1700 ecstacy tablets, 83 mandrax tablets and more than 98 grams of cocaine powder in his possession. Provincial police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said police received a tip off and followed up. "When they arrived at the premises, they searched the man and found the drugs.  He was immediately arrested and charged for possession of drugs. He was taken to Point police station for detention and he will appear in the Durban Magistrates Court on Wednesday. The recovered drugs have an estimated street value of R140 000," she said. Mbele said during a second operation in Verulam, north of the city centre, seven men were arrested for two incidents. "In Verulam, police shutdown six illegal liquor outlets and the confiscated the alcohol.  The arrest of five suspects for possession of heroin capsules, two males were arrested for assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm, another suspect was arrested for armed robbery," she said. Mbele said police then proceeded to Ireland Street where they found two males with a TLB machinery suspected to be stolen. "Two males aged 36 and 37 were arrested and charged for possession of suspected stolen property. All the arrested suspects will appear in the Verulam Magistrates Court on Wednesday," she said. The Mercury